From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Patric Stout <github@truebrain.nl>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 23:41:24 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] chore: include all required system headers

Linux compilers tend to be more strict in what headers
they need, where other compilers tend to auto-include
some.
---
 src/pch.h | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/pch.h b/src/pch.h
index 399ad62..5132570 100644
--- a/src/pch.h
+++ b/src/pch.h
@@ -12,3 +12,5 @@
 #include <sstream>
 #include <cmath>
 #include <charconv>
+#include <cstring>
+#include <algorithm>
